# React Component Conventions

## Server vs Client Components

Default to **Server Components** (no directive needed). Add `'use client'` only when the component:
- Uses React hooks (`useState`, `useEffect`, `useRef`, etc.)
- Handles browser events
- Accesses browser-only APIs

```tsx
// Server Component (default) — no directive
export default async function PostList() {
  const posts = await getPosts();
  return <ul>{posts.map(p => <li key={p.slug}>{p.metadata.title}</li>)}</ul>;
}

// Client Component — only when needed
'use client';
import { useState } from 'react';

export function Toggle() {
  const [open, setOpen] = useState(false);
  return <button onClick={() => setOpen(o => !o)}>{open ? 'Close' : 'Open'}</button>;
}
```

## File Structure

Reusable components use this structure:

```
components/
└── ComponentName/
    ├── index.ts           # Barrel export
    └── ComponentName.tsx  # Component logic + inline Tailwind
```

For simple single-file components, a flat file is fine:
```
components/
└── ComponentName.tsx
```

Page-level components (used only in app shell) live in `app/_components/`.

## Barrel Export

```tsx
// components/ComponentName/index.ts
export { default } from './ComponentName';
export type { ComponentNameProps } from './ComponentName';
```

## Example Component

```tsx
// components/Anchor/Anchor.tsx
import { cn } from '@/lib/utils';

export interface AnchorProps extends React.AnchorHTMLAttributes<HTMLAnchorElement> {
  external?: boolean;
}

const Anchor = ({ children, className, external, ...props }: AnchorProps) => {
  return (
    <a
      className={cn('text-link underline-offset-2 hover:underline', className)}
      {...(external ? { target: '_blank', rel: 'noopener noreferrer' } : {})}
      {...props}
    >
      {children}
    </a>
  );
};

export default Anchor;
```

## Shadcn UI Components

Shadcn primitives live in `components/ui/`. They are **generated by the CLI** — avoid manual edits.

To add a new primitive:
```bash
bunx shadcn@latest add <component>
```

Import them with the `@/components/ui` alias:
```tsx
import { Button } from '@/components/ui/button';
import { Dialog } from '@/components/ui/dialog';
```

## Icons

Use `@hugeicons/react` exclusively. Do not use lucide-react or heroicons.

```tsx
import { Home01Icon, SearchIcon } from '@hugeicons/react';

<Home01Icon size={20} strokeWidth={1.5} />
```

## MDX Components

Components available in MDX posts are registered in `mdx-components.tsx`:

```tsx
// mdx-components.tsx
import type { MDXComponents } from 'mdx/types';
import MyWidget from '@/components/MyWidget';

const components = {
  MyWidget,
  a: Anchor,
  // ...
} satisfies MDXComponents;

export function useMDXComponents(): MDXComponents {
  return components;
}
```

Use them in MDX files by JSX tag name:
```mdx
<MyWidget />
```

## Adding Animations

Use the `motion` library:

```tsx
import { motion } from 'motion/react';

<motion.div
  initial={{ opacity: 0, y: 8 }}
  animate={{ opacity: 1, y: 0 }}
  transition={{ duration: 0.3 }}
>
  Content
</motion.div>
```

For layout animations, wrap with `<AnimatePresence>`:

```tsx
import { AnimatePresence, motion } from 'motion/react';

<AnimatePresence>
  {visible && (
    <motion.div key="panel" exit={{ opacity: 0 }}>
      Content
    </motion.div>
  )}
</AnimatePresence>
```

## WebGL / OGL

OGL components are client-only. Always add `'use client'` and initialize inside `useEffect`:

```tsx
'use client';
import { useEffect, useRef } from 'react';
import { Renderer, Camera, Mesh } from 'ogl';

export function GLCanvas() {
  const canvasRef = useRef<HTMLCanvasElement>(null);

  useEffect(() => {
    const renderer = new Renderer({ canvas: canvasRef.current! });
    // setup scene...
    return () => renderer.gl.getExtension('WEBGL_lose_context')?.loseContext();
  }, []);

  return <canvas ref={canvasRef} />;
}
```

## Creating a New Component

1. Create `components/ComponentName/ComponentName.tsx` with a named prop interface
2. Apply styles with Tailwind utilities; use `cn()` for conditional classes
3. Create `components/ComponentName/index.ts` barrel export
4. If it belongs in MDX, register it in `mdx-components.tsx`

## Zustand State

Use Zustand for shared client state. Define stores in `lib/` or a dedicated `stores/` directory:

```tsx
import { create } from 'zustand';

interface ThemeStore {
  accent: string;
  setAccent: (accent: string) => void;
}

export const useThemeStore = create<ThemeStore>((set) => ({
  accent: 'violet',
  setAccent: (accent) => set({ accent }),
}));
```
